From: sid <sidgrip@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0007] baikal: explicit per-board failover pool

Adds an `ascfailover|<asc>,<pool_no>` API command + cgpu_info
failover_pool_no field. select_baikal_failover_pool_locked honors
the explicit pin first; if the explicit pool is unworkable it
returns NULL (board halts), bypassing the auto-search across all
same-algo pools. Pin survives hotplug via static table in
driver-baikalu.c, mirroring the existing primary pin storage.

